.TH BEEP(1),User Commands,BEEP(1)

.SH NAME
beep - emit a terminal bell

.SH SYNOPSIS
beep

.SH DESCRIPTION
beep writes a single bell character (ASCII 7) to the terminal.
On systems with an audible bell, this produces a short tone;
on visual-bell terminals, it produces a brief screen flash instead.
beep takes no options or arguments.

.SH EXIT STATUS
beep always exits 0.
